Chapter 2 Filesystems

To check in which directory you are currently in use this command
pwd(print working directory)

To list all the sub-directories or files in the main directory use this command
ls(List)

To switch between the directories use the command
cd to move to another directory use cd directoryname if want to comeback use cd ..

An absolute file path will always start with a slash / and the relative path will not start with slash

The cat command is used to view the contents of a file. It's short for "concatenate," which is a fancy way of saying "put things together.
" It can feel like a confusing name if you're using the cat command to view a single file, but it makes more sense when you're using it
to view multiple files at once.
